Obj1----->m1()--->obj2
then obj2 responds with hello!
Now will add obj3 and all the 3 have to interact .
So obj1 will have reference of the obj2 and obj3 and similarly with the other two.
and as number of objects increases, the number of references of other objects , an object has to keep also increases
and objects also get tightly coupled.
To avoid this we use Mediator Design Pattern.
lets say have 4 objects.. obj1, obj2,obj3,obj4
And we will have an MEDIATIOR OBJECT.
The 4 objects doesnt have any reference of other objects. They have only reference of mediator object.
MEDIATOR Object has reference to all the four objects.
If obj1 has something like send(obj4, msg) and gives it MEDIATOR then, MEDIATOR sends that to obj4.
MEDIATOR helps in interacting between objects.
No more tight coupling due to MEDIATOR OBJECT.


Defines an object that encapsulates how a set of objects interact, and promote loose coupling by preventing them from referring to each other.